Popular Kayamata merchant, Jaruma who was recently arrested, has declared herself Nigeria’s President-in-waiting. Jaruma made the claim in a short video while confirming the news of her arrest by the police in Abuja after it went viral. According to the aphrodisiac seller, Obasanjo and Buhari served jail time before emerging President, saying she was toying the same path. “The only thing I have to say about this is President Obasanjo was in prison. He came out of prison and became President. President Buhari was in prison, he came out and became President.   AFCON 2021: Why I stopped watching football – Naira Marley     I miss bachelorhood, says D’banj     Nine Yoruba actors/actresses who remarried   - Advertisement - “By God’s grace, for this, guys you know who the next president of Nigeria is going to be. It’s your girl, Jaruma. It’s a pattern oh.” Jaruma has also updated her Instagram bio to reflect her assertion. She wrote: “1st female President of Nigeria”